OL,4,CMenstrual leave: South Korea airline
OL,5,Cboss fined for refusing time off
OL,6, A former airline CEO who refused to
OL,7, allow female staff to take menstrual
OL,8, leave protected by employment law has
OL,9, been fined almost $1,800 (#1,300; 2m
OL,10, won) by a court in South Korea.
OL,12,FKim Soo-cheon, the ex-head of Asiana
OL,13,FAirlines, turned down 138 requests from
OL,14,F15 flight attendants in 2014 and 2015.
OL,16,FMr Kim claimed the employees did not
OL,17,Fprovide proof of menstruation.
OL,19,FSince 1953, women in South Korea have
OL,20,Fbeen allowed to take one day off a
OL,21,Fmonth if they have painful periods.
